info.headline: Flood Watch issued May 12 at 2:19PM CDT until further notice by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH FRIDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues to be possible. Areas of Cook county are seeing minor flooding on area roadways. * WHERE...Portions of east central Minnesota, north central Minnesota and northeast Minnesota, including the following areas, Crow Wing, Aitkin, Koochiching, Cass, Itasca. In northeast Minnesota, Carlton and St. Louis, Cook and Lake counties. * WHEN...Through Friday morning. * IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations. Creeks and streams may rise out of their banks. Flooding may occur in poor drainage and urban areas. Over portions of Lake and Cook County, snow melt will add to runoff increasing the flooding potential. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - Thunderstorms Wednesday evening and early Thursday morning have led to widespread precipitation accumulations from 0.75 to 1.25 inches across northern Minnesota. Rivers, especially those north of Highway 2 and along the North Shore are already exhibiting rises on top of pre-existing high flows. Another 1-1.5" of precipitation is forecast to fall over this same area in the next 12 hours. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared to take action should flooding develop.
